events.name: HACKRUSH - fridays
events.description:
HackRush is an initiative formed by the community leaders in DeKUT and collaboration with DeHUB to give students a chance to experience how a Hack-A-Thon is run and established. Its main purpose is to Learn, Build, Share and Evolve.

We group students into their level of experience and pair them with experts so the can have interactive sessions and learn by building products during the 12 Hours.

Come and join us for interactive session about code!

events.name: DevFest Nairobi 2017
events.description:
GDG DevFest 2017 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas, codelabs, hackathon and more!

Joining thousands all over the world for the greatest series of DevFest events DevFest Nairobi and Central Google Developer Groups are coming together to have the biggest developer event of the year! aimed at familiarizing attendees (who are members of a variety of developer communities) with groundbreaking technology advancements. We will be working closely with Women Techmakers in this devfest season, to continue improving the diversity in our ecosystem.

We are delighted to host the biggest Devfest in Sub Saharan Africa this year alongside other communities in Nairobi and Central Kenya! This year on 11th November 2017 at Strathmore University, we'll be opening doors to hundreds of developers from all over the globe and we can't wait to host you! We have over 20 sessions, codelabs and talks by exemplary contributors in the tech scene. Everything from IoT, Machine learning, DevOps, Design and so much more.

If you have RSVPd for the event on the meetup group, please make sure that you have registered for a ticket on this link. https://goo.gl/bXAU95­

*an RSVP on meetup will not guarantee your entry to the venue, only your Eventbrite ticket will

events.name: NOODLERS CAMP
events.description:
GDG Nyeri will be partnering with Intel and the Computer Society of Kimathi to host the Noodlers Camp '18. The event will take place at the Dedan Kimathi University Auditorium on Saturday 12th May as from 9.00AM.

The theme of the event is to showcase Google as the Computer Society of Kimathi will invite new members to join the club.
This year's Noodlers Camp will be the 6th since the club was formed in 2012.

Key speakers will be from GDG Nyeri, Intel Ambassador and CSK Officials.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam 2019
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us, Women Techmakers Nyeri, for our Cloud Study Jam! 🔥

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

1. Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.

2. Don’t forget your charger.😊

3. Curiosity and eagerness to learn something new 💯

It's 3 hours of Learning and Endless Fun🤗💯

events.name: IWD19 Extended Nyeri
events.description:
Google’s Women Techmakers program is supporting and empowering women in technology through an annual global event series in celebration of International Women’s Day (IWD).
International Womens Day is a day set aside to celebrate women in STEM around the globe.

This year we'll be privileged to hold our first ever IWD extended in Nyeri. There will be workshops,codelabs,talks and also amazing networking.

We will be glad to have you!

Bring a laptop, positive energy and a friend.

events.name: GDG DevFest Nyeri 2019
events.description:
GDG DevFest Nyeri 2019 is an amazing event that is aimed at bringing together all the developers, tech enthusiasts and persons in unrelated careers but with interest in tech from Central and beyond for an entire day of learning about and interacting with Google technologies. There will be a series of sessions on various development paths such as Android, Web, Emerging technologies like Artificial Intelligence and Cloud Computing, and many others which will be led by experts in the industry.

upcoming.name: Women + Technology : Solving the Puzzle of Being a Woman in Tech
upcoming.description:
Are you a Woman in Tech? Or, are you wondering how you can begin your career in Tech? Are you stuck in your journey of learning programming?
Are you confused at what programming language to get started with?

If you answered yes to any of the questions, then you are just the person we are looking for!

In this session, we will cover how you can begin your journey in tech by getting you started in programming, exposing you to alternate tech fields that you can explore, provide you with the tools you need to get started, and if you are stuck, then we can help unblock you by answering your questions, and giving you the resources to help you solve the problem and continue creating more solutions for the community ☺️.

All you will need to have is a laptop, a notebook and a pen, lots of curiosity and googling skills 😉

Bring your friends with you and let's rock this table 💃

upcoming.name: #IAmRemarkable : Mastering the Art of Self-Promotion
upcoming.description:
#IAmRemarkable💃💃💃

Women have been conditioned for aeons to be "humble" or "modest" especially when it comes to how they embrace and carry their achievements.
Furthermore, while many men can apply for an opportunity to which they are only 50% qualified, women often tend to shy from applying for the same unless they feel 101% qualified.
This has really hurt many careers of these women, who are many times overlooked and foregone in favor of their male counterparts.

This session will seek to teach how one can be confident about their achievements, and being comfortable sharing what they have achieved with the rest of the world. Also it will explore how we as women in tech can continually overcome imposter syndrome, strive to take more risks and how to navigate these challenges.

In addition, we are going to cover an applied skill called Public Speaking, which is skill that many of us have not grasped.

Our aim is not just to raise a community of women in tech who are badass as developers, project managers, designers or tech writers, but also who are comfortable not only taking up space, but also comfortable occupying and representing in that space!🔥🔥🔥

This session will be led by a qualified #IAmRemarkable Facilitator, and one woman guest who will be revealed soon.

Can't wait to see you there! Bring your friends too🤩

upcoming.name: IWD20: International Women's Day 2020💃
upcoming.description:
#Together We Rise #IWD #WTM

This International Women's Day💃💃💃, we’re inviting you to share your superpowers - those special qualities that make you shine. Whether you’re creating space for more voices to be heard, working towards honing your coding abilities, trying to get a career in the tech ecosystem or you’re working to secure funding as an entrepreneur, you’re a superhero in our book.

1. What is your superpower?

2. What is your superhero name?

3. What superhero do you most identify with and why?

4. What is a superpower you wish you had?

5. What is one superpower you have that no one would suspect you possess?

6. What is your power stance? What does it feel like? Look like?

7. Where do you feel most powerful? What are you doing and/or who are you with?

Together let’s celebrate the super-women in our lives. Together let’s create a new narrative for our industry. #TogetherWeRise.🔥🔥

NOTE: Everyone is Invited 🤗 And you don't have to know how to code. We will teach you this skill, so just bring your enthusiasm, curiosity and superpowers.
